WEBVTT

00:21.563 --> 00:23.440
[theme music playing]

02:10.338 --> 02:12.006
I can't believe this is happening.

02:12.090 --> 02:13.758
I cannot believe I let you do this.

02:14.467 --> 02:16.219
-We all agreed.
-I didn't.

02:16.761 --> 02:19.013
-We decided it was worth the risk.
-This is a mistake.

02:19.097 --> 02:21.057
This is how amateurs get caught.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.225
Nomi, help.

02:22.308 --> 02:25.145
Will, it's going to be fine.
The ID held up.

02:25.228 --> 02:27.480
In England. Outgoing.

02:27.564 --> 02:29.649
It is never the same as Incoming.

02:30.441 --> 02:33.319
We're inside the TSA,
watching for any alert.

02:33.403 --> 02:34.487
[Amanita] Any better?

02:34.571 --> 02:35.655
Unh-unh.

02:35.738 --> 02:38.324
You're in the woods.
You barely have Wi-Fi.

02:38.408 --> 02:42.704
-Bug's on it.
-Color the Bug totally clustered.

02:42.787 --> 02:43.746
[Amanita] Hi, Bug.

02:44.330 --> 02:45.456
What's up, Neets?

02:46.166 --> 02:47.417
Can I get you anything?

02:48.877 --> 02:49.878
Earplugs.

02:50.378 --> 02:52.589
Okay. I heard that.
And they're not gonna work

02:52.672 --> 02:54.465
because I'm talking inside your head.

02:55.008 --> 02:57.719
She knows. She didn't mean it literally.

02:59.679 --> 03:03.099
And you know he's only freaking out
because he loves you so much.

03:06.019 --> 03:08.605
You can't do anything now.
Let's let her sleep.

03:10.440 --> 03:12.025
Okay, dinner's ready.

03:12.108 --> 03:13.276
Oh, we're coming.

03:13.902 --> 03:16.946
Bug, anything happens,
no matter how small, you call me.

03:17.030 --> 03:18.740
Bug's on duty.

03:18.823 --> 03:20.783
You know, this whole visiting thing?

03:20.867 --> 03:23.077
It's a little like FaceTime
without a phone.

03:23.161 --> 03:25.079
Ha! That's what I said!

03:25.163 --> 03:27.206
-[beeping]
-Uh-oh.

03:27.290 --> 03:28.791
What? Wait, what?

03:28.875 --> 03:32.420
-TSA bumped up its warning level.
-Why?

03:32.503 --> 03:33.963
Another mass shooting.

03:34.047 --> 03:37.217
At this point, aren't mass shootings
just business as usual in America?

03:43.556 --> 03:44.724
[sighs]

03:56.361 --> 03:57.654
Please be careful.

04:00.740 --> 04:01.950
I will.

04:17.924 --> 04:19.634
Ma'am! He's in a meeting.

04:19.717 --> 04:21.177
This is more important.

04:22.720 --> 04:25.014
-[Rajan] ...less humid in those countries.
-[Kala] Oh, my God.

04:25.098 --> 04:26.891
-Kala.
-I'm interrupting again.

04:26.975 --> 04:27.976
No, no, no, no.

04:28.059 --> 04:30.979
You've just turned an unbearably boring
piece of business

04:31.062 --> 04:32.855
into another rare pleasure.

04:33.523 --> 04:36.192
-I will come back.
-Mrs. Rasal, the priority is obvious here.

04:36.276 --> 04:39.195
And Raj, I must say, you're spending
too much time with me

04:39.279 --> 04:43.741
when you have a bride this beautiful
right here in the very same building.

04:45.034 --> 04:47.537
It makes me think I taught you nothing
at school, my friend.

04:48.413 --> 04:49.872
One of us has to work, Ajay.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.041
See you later.

04:53.293 --> 04:56.087
-Mrs. Rasal.
-[Rajan] Come, Kala.

04:57.964 --> 05:01.718
These shipping reports
have been falsified. Everything.

05:01.801 --> 05:04.762
Everything that the controller
is approving has been doctored.

05:04.846 --> 05:07.223
The manifests are complete lies!

05:08.266 --> 05:11.311
My God, Kala, you are even more beautiful
when you're upset.

05:11.394 --> 05:14.063
Rajan, please.
We're shipping out old antibiotics,

05:14.147 --> 05:15.815
discontinued HIV inhibitors.

05:15.898 --> 05:19.444
We're selling old, useless, defective,
and possibly poisonous drugs

05:19.527 --> 05:21.612
to people whose lives depend on them.

05:22.113 --> 05:24.115
I know this is not easy to hear
for the first time,

05:24.198 --> 05:26.284
but this is all standard procedure.

05:27.702 --> 05:29.871
We have to vacate our storage space.

05:29.954 --> 05:33.416
And our profit margins,
like every pharma company,

05:33.499 --> 05:36.919
depend on not wasting every drug
that's slightly below standard.

05:38.629 --> 05:39.797
You know?

05:39.881 --> 05:42.759
This is how this business works.
We all do it.

05:43.217 --> 05:45.136
Some of those drugs can still work.

05:45.636 --> 05:48.639
We are selling the only kind
that those people can afford.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.308
You have to trust me.

05:51.267 --> 05:53.186
This is the way to serve the greater good.

05:54.145 --> 05:56.439
What if your father
or what if I went to a hospital

05:56.522 --> 05:58.775
and was given improper, expired drugs?

06:01.027 --> 06:02.612
-That won't happen.
-Why not?

06:03.946 --> 06:06.699
Because these products
are shipped to distant places.

06:06.783 --> 06:09.118
We would never risk the lives
of our own people.

06:09.619 --> 06:11.079
Which places?

06:12.288 --> 06:15.750
Out of India. You know,
like China or Africa,

06:15.833 --> 06:17.126
faraway places.

06:21.547 --> 06:22.840
Like Kenya?

06:24.133 --> 06:25.468
Could be. Why?

06:35.311 --> 06:36.145
Kala?

07:11.055 --> 07:12.348
Have you seen this?

07:17.270 --> 07:19.188
So many terrible things going on.

07:22.400 --> 07:26.362
I used to wonder if there was something
I could do to try to change the world...

07:28.364 --> 07:31.659
before I understood such thoughts
were unskilled.

07:34.662 --> 07:37.915
Trying to change the world
only leads to suffering.

07:39.584 --> 07:41.752
All we can change is ourselves.

07:45.798 --> 07:47.425
I'm not sure I agree.

07:48.593 --> 07:49.635
I know.

07:51.137 --> 07:52.930
That's why I can't help you.

07:56.976 --> 07:59.437
You weren't sitting in that seat before,
were you?

08:00.271 --> 08:02.607
I hope one day we can visit again...

08:03.858 --> 08:06.569
when your thinking does not reflect
their thinking.

08:06.652 --> 08:08.237
No, please, talk to me.

08:09.071 --> 08:10.323
You were at the rave.

08:11.949 --> 08:14.744
I don't understand.
Why can't I see where you are?

08:14.827 --> 08:18.122
You may feel gravity
without knowing how it works.

08:20.166 --> 08:23.294
There are forces acting upon every life

08:23.377 --> 08:26.589
that remain beyond our control
or comprehension.

08:42.063 --> 08:43.314
[sighs]

08:43.397 --> 08:46.234
I think we can all agree that things
were much different back then.

08:46.317 --> 08:48.444
Oh, so different.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.821
There were none of these mass shootings.

08:51.364 --> 08:54.951
-Oh, God. Did you see the terrible news?
-We just heard about it.

08:55.034 --> 08:57.245
They always want to blame it
on a religion,

08:57.328 --> 08:59.497
an ethnic group, or a skin color,

08:59.580 --> 09:02.124
but the one thing no one ever
wants to say--

09:02.208 --> 09:04.669
-It's always a man.
-Some fucking dude not getting any.

09:04.752 --> 09:06.754
Violence has a gender.

09:07.255 --> 09:09.131
Oh, my God. I love your dads.

09:09.715 --> 09:14.011
I find it fascinating how every generation
believes in different things.

09:14.095 --> 09:17.306
-We believed in pot. And sex.
-[laughter]

09:17.390 --> 09:19.141
