16:32.116 --> 16:34.952
[indistinct chatter]

16:39.456 --> 16:43.043
[indistinct singing]

16:51.051 --> 16:53.262
[woman] Five, six, seven, eight!

17:02.896 --> 17:04.023
[Capheus] Mama?

17:07.568 --> 17:09.778
-Ah. Hello, my son.
-Hi, Mom.

17:10.612 --> 17:14.408
-This is Zakia, the girl I was...
-Ah! [laughs]

17:14.491 --> 17:16.452
Yes, of course.

17:16.535 --> 17:18.287
It's wonderful to finally meet you.

17:18.370 --> 17:19.580
It's great to meet you, too.

17:19.663 --> 17:22.458
Capheus told me about the work
that you do here with the kids.

17:22.541 --> 17:24.460
It is amazing.

17:24.543 --> 17:27.379
These children do far much more for us
than we could ever do for them.

17:27.463 --> 17:31.967
So the school focuses on teaching kids
different kinds of art?

17:32.051 --> 17:37.389
Yes. Art is fundamental to the development
of a child's imagination.

17:37.473 --> 17:42.186
One cannot create or achieve anything
unless they imagine it first.

17:42.269 --> 17:44.730
My son tells me
that you were educated in London?

17:44.813 --> 17:46.982
-Yes.
-What a gift.

17:47.066 --> 17:48.233
It was.

17:48.942 --> 17:52.154
He said that you were offered many jobs
but you decided to come back home.

17:52.237 --> 17:54.114
I know there's a lot of work to do here.

17:54.198 --> 17:58.202
There's too much injustice,
too much corruption, too much poverty.

17:58.285 --> 18:01.163
But I love Kenya, like your son does.

18:01.246 --> 18:02.623
My future is my country.

18:03.540 --> 18:07.211
Which is why I am so excited
about him running for office.

18:09.129 --> 18:09.963
What?

18:11.090 --> 18:11.924
Uh...

18:16.011 --> 18:19.014
Mama, I've been meaning
to tell you something.

18:24.103 --> 18:27.106
I used to sit here and think so much
about the future...

18:27.689 --> 18:30.442
trying to picture what my life
would be like.

18:33.070 --> 18:34.988
I never imagined anything like this.

18:36.824 --> 18:39.618
I don't think anyone knows
what life they will live.

18:41.203 --> 18:46.333
-That's what makes life feel alive.
-Hm...

18:48.335 --> 18:53.215
Do you think that is also true for people,
and if it is,

18:53.298 --> 18:56.260
does that mean that you can never
really know your own husband?

18:57.719 --> 18:59.304
Or your own brother.

19:03.350 --> 19:06.645
I have to admit, I'm very uncomfortable
with this level of uncertainty.

19:07.271 --> 19:10.440
No, but what is the alternative?

19:13.402 --> 19:14.236
[Priya] Kala?

19:15.696 --> 19:16.822
You have a visitor.

19:17.322 --> 19:18.490
We can stay with you.

19:18.574 --> 19:20.159
No, it's all right.

19:21.451 --> 19:22.870
We need to talk.

19:28.333 --> 19:29.877
-Hm?
-Hm.

19:34.923 --> 19:38.760
So you got these different voices
in your head, and one of them is Will?

19:39.803 --> 19:42.764
-I know it sounds strange.
-[chuckles]

19:44.933 --> 19:46.518
If he's in your head listening,

19:47.102 --> 19:49.730
does that mean he can hear
everything I'm saying?

19:50.772 --> 19:51.899
-Yeah.
-Yes.

19:53.859 --> 19:59.615
So when I say, "Go take a flying fuck
at a rolling doughnut, Gorski,"

20:00.199 --> 20:01.200
he can hear that?

20:01.700 --> 20:02.743
Yeah.

20:03.493 --> 20:04.578
I deserve it.

20:05.078 --> 20:06.955
He says he deserves it.

20:07.039 --> 20:08.290
Damn right he does.

20:08.999 --> 20:11.501
